<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype
 id="_x0000_t75" coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t"
 path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" filled="f" stroked="f">
 <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
 <v:formulas>
  <v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @6 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @8 21600 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"/>
 </v:formulas>
 <v:path o:extrusionok="f" gradientshapeok="t" o:connecttype="rect"/>
 <o:lock v:ext="edit" aspectratio="t"/>
</v:shapetype><v:shape id="_x0000_i1028" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:495.75pt;
 height:80.25pt' filled="t">
 <v:fill color2="black"/>
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./a_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
 <v:textbox inset="0,0,0,0"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=661 height=107
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./a_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1028"><![endif]><b><span
style='font-size:20.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<h3><span style='font-size:28.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt'>Problem A<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:20.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt;font-family:
Arial'>Game  Mouse and Cheese </span></b><span style='font-family:Arial'><br>
<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Input: </b><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>Standard Input</span><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><o:p></o:p></b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Output: </span></b><span
style='font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Standard Output<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText3><br>
SOHA and TARA have recently invented a new game called Mouse and Cheese. As
the name suggests, this game involves a mouse searching for a piece of cheese.
The game is played on a 3x3 board as shown in the diagram below. Each cell is
uniquely numbered with an integer between 1 and 9. The board contains 12 sticks
(the blue lines in the diagram).</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id="Picture_x0020_2"
 o:spid="_x0000_s2139" type="#_x0000_t75" style='position:absolute;left:0;
 text-align:left;margin-left:150.75pt;margin-top:10.3pt;width:163.5pt;height:164.25pt;
 z-index:1;visibility:visible;mso-position-horizontal:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical:absolute'>
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./a_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
 <v:textbox style='mso-rotate-with-shape:t'/>
 <w:wrap type="square" anchorx="page"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=218 height=219
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./a_files/image001.png"  align=left hspace=12 v:shapes="Picture_x0020_2"><![endif]><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:16.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id="Picture_x0020_1"
 o:spid="_x0000_s2140" type="#_x0000_t75" style='position:absolute;left:0;
 text-align:left;margin-left:0;margin-top:3.8pt;width:186pt;height:182.25pt;
 z-index:2;visibility:visible;mso-position-horizontal:left'>
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./a_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
 <v:textbox style='mso-rotate-with-shape:t'/>
 <w:wrap type="square" anchorx="page"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=248 height=243
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./a_files/image001.png"  align=left hspace=12 v:shapes="Picture_x0020_1"><![endif]><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:16.0pt'>Initially a mouse and a piece of cheese are
placed on two different cells. In the example to the right, the mouse is placed
on cell 8 and the cheese is placed on cell 3. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'>The rule of the game goes like this: Its a two-player game where the
players make moves alternately. SOHA, being player 1, goes first. In each move,
the player selects a stick and throws it away. After each move, if the mouse
can reach the cell containing the cheese without touching any of the remaining
sticks, then that player is declared as the winner? If both play perfectly, who
wins?<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'>Before the game starts, some of the sticks are removed. You will be given
the coordinates of these sticks and the cell numbers of the mouse and cheese. A
stick is represented using the coordinates of its end points. The lower left of
the grid is the origin (0, 0). The two sticks surrounding the cheese, in the
example above, has coordinates 2 0 2 1 and 2 1 3 1.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Note that the end-points of a stick can be
given in any order. That is 2 0 2 1 could be given as 2 1 2 0.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt'>Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt'>The first line of input is an integer <b>T</b>(<b>T</b>&lt;1000) that
determines the number of test cases. Each case starts with 3 integers <b>S</b>,
<b>C</b> and <b>R</b>. <b>S</b> and <b>C</b> denotes the location of the mouse
and cheese respectively. Each of the next <b>R</b> lines contains 4
space-separated integers that give the coordinates of the sticks removed from
the board before the start of the game.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><u><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>Notes and
Constraints<br>
</span></u><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'>1
&lt;= S,C &lt;= 9<br>
S != C<br>
0 &lt;= R &lt;= 12</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>For each case, all
the removed sticks will be distinct.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt'>Output<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'>For each case, output the case number first, starting with 1, followed
by the name of the player who wins. If the mouse can already reach the cheese
before the game starts, output No Cheese! instead. Look at the samples for
exact format.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<table border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 style='border-collapse:collapse;
 border:none;mso-border-alt:solid black .5pt;mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
 <tr>
  <td width=319 valign=top style='width:239.4pt;border:solid black .5pt;
  padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoHeading7><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:20.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:
  Arial'>Sample Input<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width=319 valign=top style='width:239.4pt;border:solid black .5pt;
  border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid black .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:20.0pt;
  font-family:Arial'>Output for Sample Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td width=319 valign=top style='width:239.4pt;border:solid black .5pt;
  border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid black .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'>3<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=MsoNormal><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'>1
  2 1<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=MsoNormal><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'>1
  1 1 0<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=MsoNormal><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'>1
  4 0<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;page-break-before:
always'><b><span style='font-size:20.0pt'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id="_x0000_t75"
 coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t" path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe"
 filled="f" stroked="f">
 <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
 <v:formulas>
  <v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @6 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @8 21600 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"/>
 </v:formulas>
 <v:path o:extrusionok="f" gradientshapeok="t" o:connecttype="rect"/>
 <o:lock v:ext="edit" aspectratio="t"/>
</v:shapetype><v:shape id="_x0000_i1030" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:495.75pt;
 height:78.75pt' filled="t">
 <v:fill color2="black"/>
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
 <v:textbox inset="0,0,0,0"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=661 height=105
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1030"><![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<h3><span style='font-size:28.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt'>Problem B<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:20.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt;font-family:
Arial'>Bisectors </span></b><span style='font-family:Arial'><br>
<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Input: </b><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>Standard Input</span><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><o:p></o:p></b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Output: </span></b><span
style='font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Standard Output</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-family:Arial'><br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
<![if !supportLineBreakNewLine]><br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
<![endif]></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>We all probably know how to find equation
of bisectors in Coordinate Geometry. If the equations of two lines are <sub><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape
 id="_x0000_i1031" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:98.25pt;height:21.75pt'
 o:ole=" >
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=131 height=29
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1031"><![endif]></sub><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>
 <o:OLEObject Type="Embed" ProgID="Equation.3" ShapeID="_x0000_i1031"
  DrawAspect="Content" ObjectID="_1344844691">
 </o:OLEObject>
</xml><![endif]--><span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span>and <sub><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape
 id="_x0000_i1032" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:104.25pt;height:23.25pt'
 o:ole=" >
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=139 height=31
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1032"><![endif]></sub><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>
 <o:OLEObject Type="Embed" ProgID="Equation.3" ShapeID="_x0000_i1032"
  DrawAspect="Content" ObjectID="_1344844692">
 </o:OLEObject>
</xml><![endif]-->, then the equations of the bisectors of the four angles they
create are given by<sub><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id="_x0000_i1033" type="#_x0000_t75"
 style='width:189.75pt;height:48.75pt' o:ole=" >
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=253 height=65
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1033"><![endif]></sub><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>
 <o:OLEObject Type="Embed" ProgID="Equation.3" ShapeID="_x0000_i1033"
  DrawAspect="Content" ObjectID="_1344844693">
 </o:OLEObject>
</xml><![endif]-->. Now one has to be quite intelligent to find out for which
angles to choose the +(plus) sign and for which angles to choose the
-(minus) sign. You will have to do similar sort of choosing in this problem.
Suppose there is a fixed point (C<sub>x</sub>, C<sub>y</sub>) and there are n
(n&#8804;10000) other points around it. No two points from these n points are
collinear with (C<sub>x</sub>, C<sub>y</sub>). If you connect all these point
with (C<sub>x</sub>, C<sub>y</sub>) you will get a star-topology like image
made of n lines. The equations of these n lines are also given and only these
equations must be used when finding the equation of bisectors. This n lines
create n(n-1)/2 acute or obtuse angles in total and so they have total n(n-1)/2
bisectors. You have to find out how many of these bisectors have equations
formed using the + sign. The image below shows an image where n=5, C<sub>x</sub>=5
and C<sub>y</sub>=2. This image corresponds to the only sample input.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span></p>

<div align=center>

<table border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 style='border-collapse:collapse;
 border:none;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
 <tr>
  <td width=546 valign=top style='width:409.45pt;border:solid windowtext .5pt;
  padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><!--[if gte vml 1]><o:wrapblock><v:shape
    id="_x0000_s2094" type="#_x0000_t75" style='position:absolute;left:0;
    text-align:left;margin-left:1.45pt;margin-top:-286.45pt;width:299.9pt;
    height:268.1pt;z-index:1'>
    <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
    <w:wrap type="topAndBottom" anchorx="page"/>
   </v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><span style='mso-ignore:vglayout'>
   <table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
    <tr>
     <td width=2 height=0></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td></td>
     <td><img width=400 height=358 src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_s2094"></td>
    </tr>
   </table>
   </span><![endif]><!--[if gte vml 1]></o:wrapblock><![endif]--><br
  style='mso-ignore:vglayout' clear=ALL>
  </p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td width=546 valign=top style='width:409.45pt;border:solid windowtext .5pt;
  border-top:none;mso-border-top-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal>Figure: Five lines above create 5(5-1)/2=10 angles and
  these angles has 10 bisectors. Of these 10 bisectors, the equation of only 4 are
  formed using the + sign of the formula <sub><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id="_x0000_i1034"
   type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:189.75pt;height:48.75pt' o:ole=" >
   <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
  </v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=253 height=65
  src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1034"><![endif]></sub><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>
    <o:OLEObject Type="Embed" ProgID="Equation.3" ShapeID="_x0000_i1034"
        DrawAspect="Content" ObjectID="_1344844694">
	   </o:OLEObject></o:OLEObject>
  </xml><![endif]--></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

</div>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<h6><span class=StyleArial16pt><span style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:
12.5pt;font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Input</span></span><span
class=StyleArial16pt><span style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.5pt;
mso-ascii-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:"Arial Unicode MS";
mso-hansi-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><o:p></o:p></span></span></h6>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:.5in'>The input file contains maximum 35
sets of inputs. The description of each set is given below:</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>First line of each set contains three integers C<sub><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:16.0pt'>x</span></sub>, C<sub><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'>y</span></sub> (-10000 &#8804;<span style='font-family:"Angsana New"'> </span>C<sub><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:16.0pt'>x</span></sub>, C<sub><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'>y</span></sub> &#8804; 10000) and n (0 &#8804; n &#8804; <br>
10000).<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Each of the next n lines
contains two integers xi, yi (20000 &#8804; xi, yi &#8804; 20000) and a string
of the form a<sub><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:16.0pt'>i</span></sub>x+b<sub><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:16.0pt'>i</span></sub>y+c<sub><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
16.0pt'>i</span></sub>=0. Here (xi, yi) is the coordinate of a point around
(Cx, Cy) and the string denotes the equation of the line segment formed by
connecting (C<sub><span style='font-size:14.0pt'>x</span></sub>, C<sub><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:16.0pt'>y</span></sub>) and (xi, yi). You can assume
that (-100000 &#8804; a<sub><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:16.0pt'>i</span></sub>,
b<sub><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:16.0pt'>i</span></sub> &#8804; 100000)
and (-2000000000 &#8804; c<sub><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:16.0pt'>i</span></sub>
&#8804; 2000000000). This equation will actually be used to find the equations
of bisectors of the angles that this line creates.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Input is terminated by a set where the value of n is zero.</p>

<h4 style='margin-left:0in;text-indent:0in'><span class=StyleArial16pt><span
style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial'>Output </span></span><span
class=StyleArial16pt><span style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:16.0pt;
mso-ascii-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-hansi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><o:p></o:p></span></span></h4>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;tab-stops:143.25pt'><span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">             </span>For each<span style='color:black'>
set </span>of input produce one line of output. This line contains an integer
number P that denotes of the <sub><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape
 id="_x0000_i1035" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:42pt;height:30.75pt' o:ole=" >
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=56 height=41
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1035"><![endif]></span></sub><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>
 <o:OLEObject Type="Embed" ProgID="Equation.3" ShapeID="_x0000_i1035"
  DrawAspect="Content" ObjectID="_1344844695">
 </o:OLEObject>
</xml><![endif]--><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'><span
style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span>bisector equations how many are formed using
the + sign in the bisector equation </span><sub><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape
 id="_x0000_i1036" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:189.75pt;height:48.75pt'
 o:ole=" >
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=253 height=65
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1036"><![endif]></sub><span
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>
 <o:OLEObject Type="Embed" ProgID="Equation.3" ShapeID="_x0000_i1036"
  DrawAspect="Content" ObjectID="_1344844696">
 </o:OLEObject>
</xml><![endif]--></span>.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;tab-stops:92.4pt'><span
style='mso-tab-count:5'>                                                                        </span></p>

<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:20.0pt'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype
 id="_x0000_t75" coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t"
 path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" filled="f" stroked="f">
 <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
 <v:formulas>
  <v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"/>

  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"/>

  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>

</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=661 height=111

<h3><span style='font-size:28.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt'>Problem C<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:20.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt;font-family:
Arial'>Warp Speed </span></b><span style='font-family:Arial'><br>
<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Input: </b><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>Standard Input</span><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><o:p></o:p></b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Output: </span></b><span
style='font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Standard Output</span><b><span
style='font-size:16.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;text-align:justify;
mso-hyphenate:auto'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:
Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>In the not-so-distance future, space
engineers can invent a new technology for traveling through space and name it as
warp-drive. This warp-drive can make a spaceship travel faster than light
speed. It works by bending an amount of distance in space and make a ship
travel through that bended space in a single hop. And since the time spent
for each hop is equal, the total traveling time for any spaceship (that is
equipped with this warp-drive) depends on the number of hops it make. Moreover,
these engineers notice that distance of a hop depends on some kind of force
fields in the space where that hop is operated. To travel from a beginning to
an ending point, a spaceship may have to pass through many force fields, which
may make that spaceship hop so many times. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-hyphenate:auto'><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:
EN-US'>And from their experiments, they found some facts as follow.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-list:l18 level1 lfo7;
     mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
     12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>A number of
     force field types is quite small. <o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <ul type=circle>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-list:l18 level2 lfo7;
      mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
      12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>So <u>one
      English character</u> can be used to name each of these force filed
      types.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 </ul>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;text-align:justify;
     mso-list:l18 level1 lfo7;mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:
     EN-US'>A spaceship can pass through every single force field in a single
     hop. <o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;text-align:justify;
     mso-list:l18 level1 lfo7;mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list .5in'><span
     style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:
     EN-US'>A spaceship can pass through a certain sequences of two or more force
     fields in a single hop. And these certain sequences are kept as rules of
     single-hop-able sequences.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <ul type=circle>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;text-align:justify;
      mso-list:l18 level2 lfo7;mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><span
      style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:
      EN-US'>An example of list of these rules is shown as in the following
      table.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 </ul>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;margin-left:.75in;mso-hyphenate:
auto'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;
mso-fareast-language:EN-US'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<table border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="46%" style='width:46.46%;
 mso-cellspacing:0in;margin-left:1.5in;border:outset black .75pt;mso-padding-alt:
 3.0pt 3.0pt 3.0pt 3.0pt'>
 <tr>
  <td width="100%" valign=top style='width:100.0%;border:inset black .75pt;
  padding:3.0pt 3.0pt 3.0pt 3.0pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;text-align:
  center;mso-hyphenate:auto'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:
  Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>Rules of Single-hop-able Sequences<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td width="100%" valign=top style='width:100.0%;border:inset black .75pt;
  padding:3.0pt 3.0pt 3.0pt 3.0pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal>ab</p>
  <p class=MsoNormal>abcd</p>
  <p class=MsoNormal>abd</p>
  <p class=MsoNormal>bde<span style='mso-fareast-language:EN-US'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

<ul type=disc>
 <ul type=circle>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;text-align:justify;
      mso-list:l20 level2 lfo10;mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><span
      style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:
      EN-US'>In this example, there are 4 rules, which means that a spaceship
      can pass through each of them using a single hop. The first one is ab,
      which means that a spaceship can pass through 'a' and 'b' force field in
      a single hop. The second one is abcd which means that it can pass
      through 'a', 'b', 'c' and 'd' in one hop. <o:p></o:p></span></li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;text-align:justify;
      mso-list:l20 level2 lfo10;mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list 1.0in'><span
      style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:
      EN-US'>Please be notified that there is no abc sequence/rule in this
      example, so even though the ship can pass through abcd sequence, it is
      unable to pass through abc (in a single hop). It has to make 2 hops,
      the first hop is to pass through ab sequence and the second hop is to
      pass through c force field. <o:p></o:p></span></li>
 </ul>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial;
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Goal<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:.5in'>Suppose that you are an engineer on
a battle spaceship. Your duty is to drive your spaceship<span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'> through space as fast as possible. Your
spaceship has a probe device that can identify a sequence of force fields along
the path to your destination. In order to accomplish your duty, you have to
build a computer program to find the minimum hop based on rules and any given
sequences of force fields.</span><span style='mso-fareast-language:EN-US'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-hyphenate:auto'><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:
EN-US'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial;
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial;
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:.5in'>Input<span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'> is standard inputs which contain 2 parts of
data which are separated by a blank line.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-hyphenate:auto'><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:
EN-US'>The first part is a set of rules of single-hop-able sequences. The
number of rules is between 1 and 10,000.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-list:l21 level1 lfo13;
     mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
     12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>Each line
     in this first part contains one rule.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-list:l21 level1 lfo13;
     mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
     12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>Each rule
     is a (sub)sequence of force fields specified by a string of alphabets
     (a-z, A-Z).<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-list:l21 level1 lfo13;
     mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
     12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>The order
     in every (sub)sequence is from left to right.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-list:l21 level1 lfo13;
     mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
     12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>The size of
     any (sub)sequence is between 2 and 20.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-hyphenate:auto'><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:
EN-US'>The second part is a set of force fields along path that a spaceship has
to pass through. The number of sequence is between 1 and 200.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-list:l16 level1 lfo16;
     mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
     12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>Each line
     in this second part contains one sequence of force field in one path.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-list:l16 level1 lfo16;
     mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
     12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>Each
     sequence is specified by a string of alphabets (a-z, A-Z).<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-list:l16 level1 lfo16;
     mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
     12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>The order
     in every sequence is from left to right.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-list:l16 level1 lfo16;
     mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
     12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>The size of
     any sequence is between 2 and 500.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-hyphenate:auto'><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:
EN-US'>The blank line after the second part is the termination of the input.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial;
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Output<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:.25in'>For each sequence<span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'> in the second part
of input, write 2 parts of output as follows<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<ul type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-list:l22 level1 lfo19;
     mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
     12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>In the
     first line, write the total number of solutions followed by a space and
     the number of minimum hops.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-list:l22 level1 lfo19;
     mso-hyphenate:auto;tab-stops:list .5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
     12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>In the
     following lines, write each of the solutions in each line. Each solution
     contains a sequence of force fields as given in the input, where a space
     is inserted between each hop sub sequences. If there are two or more
     solutions, they must be sorted by ascending and lexicographical (ASCII)
     order.<o:p></o:p></span></li>
</ul>

 mso-cellspacing:0in;border:outset black .75pt;mso-padding-alt:3.0pt 3.0pt 3.0pt 3.0pt'>
 <tr>
  <td width="50%" valign=top style='width:50.0%;border:inset black .75pt;
  padding:3.0pt 3.0pt 3.0pt 3.0pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:20.0pt;

  </td>
  <td width="50%" valign=top style='width:50.0%;border:inset black .75pt;

  font-family:Arial'>Output for Sample Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>

<div class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'>

<hr size=2 width="100%" align=center>

</div>


<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-family:Arial'>Problemsetter: Chalatip
Thumkanon</span></b><b><span style='font-size:20.0pt;font-family:Arial'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-hyphenate:auto'><b><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:
EN-US'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-hyphenate:auto'><b><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:
EN-US'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-hyphenate:auto'><b><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:
EN-US'>More Explanations</span></b><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>There are 5 rules and 5 input sequences in this sample
input.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>In the first sample output, there
is 1 solution with 2 hops. The first hop is from the first rule. </p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>In the second output, there is 1 solution
with 1 hop using the second rule for the whole sequence. </p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>In the third output, there are 2
solutions with 2 hops. Its first solution is from the 4<sup>th</sup> rule and
the second solution is from the 3<sup>rd</sup> rule. </p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>In the fourth output, there are 4
solutions with 4 hops. The first solution is applied using the 4t<sup>h</sup>
rule twice. The second and third is applied using the 3<sup>rd</sup> and 4<sup>th</sup>
rules in different position. The last solution is applied using the 3<sup>rd</sup>
rules twice</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>The last output is quite similar
to the fourth one, but it is also applied with the fifth rule in the middle of
the sequence.</p>

<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b><span
style='font-size:20.0pt'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id="_x0000_t75"
 coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t" path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe"
 filled="f" stroked="f">
 <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
 <v:formulas>
  <v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @6 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @8 21600 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"/>
 </v:formulas>
 <v:path o:extrusionok="f" gradientshapeok="t" o:connecttype="rect"/>
 <o:lock v:ext="edit" aspectratio="t"/>
</v:shapetype><v:shape id="_x0000_i1040" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:495.75pt;
 height:87.75pt' filled="t">
 <v:fill color2="black"/>
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./d_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
 <v:textbox inset="0,0,0,0"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=661 height=117
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./d_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1040"><![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<h3><span style='font-size:28.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt'>Problem D<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:20.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt;font-family:
Arial'>High-Precision Number </span></b><span style='font-family:Arial'><br>
<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Input: </b><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>Standard Input</span><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><o:p></o:p></b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Output: </span></b><span
style='font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Standard Output</span><b><span
style='font-size:16.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b><span
style='font-size:20.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt'>A number with 30 decimal digits of precision can be represented by a
structure type as shown in the examples below. It includes a 30-element integer
array (</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'>digits</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>), a single integer (</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'>decpt</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>) to represent the position of the decimal
point and an integer (or character) to represent the sign (+/-). For example,
the value -218.302869584 might be stored as<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype
 id="_x0000_t202" coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="202" path="m0,0l0,21600,21600,21600,21600,0xe">
 <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
 <v:path gradientshapeok="t" o:connecttype="rect"/>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id="_x0000_s2137"
 type="#_x0000_t202" style='position:absolute;left:0;text-align:left;

 <w:wrap anchorx="page"/>
</v:shape><v:rect id="_x0000_s2138" style='position:absolute;left:0;

</v:rect><![endif]--><![if !vml]><span style='mso-ignore:vglayout'>

<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left>
 <tr>
  <td width=11 height=5></td>

  <td height=30></td>
  <td width=73 height=30 align=left valign=top bgcolor=white style='border:
  .75pt solid white;vertical-align:top;background:white'><![endif]><![if !mso]><span
  style='position:absolute;z-index:43'>
  <table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="100%">

  </span><![endif]><![if !mso & !vml]>&nbsp;<![endif]><![if !vml]></td>

</span><![endif]><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<br style='mso-ignore:vglayout' clear=ALL>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in'>Your task is to write
a program to calculate the sum of high-precision numbers.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;
font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in'><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>The first line contains a positive integer </span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:"Courier New"'>n</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'> (</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'>1&#8804;</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:"Courier New"'>n</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'>&#8804;100</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt'>) indicating the number of groups of high-precision numbers (maximum 30
significant digits). Each group includes high-precision numbers (one number in
a line) and a line with only 0 indicating the end of each group. A group can
contain 100 numbers at most.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='font-size:16.0pt;
font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;
font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Output<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>For each group, print out the sum of high-precision numbers
(one value in a line). All zeros after the decimal point located behind the
last non-zero digit must be discarded</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;page-break-before:
always;tab-stops:143.25pt'><b><span style='font-size:20.0pt'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype
 id="_x0000_t75" coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t"
 path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" filled="f" stroked="f">
 <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
 <v:formulas>
  <v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @6 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @8 21600 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"/>
 </v:formulas>
 <v:path o:extrusionok="f" gradientshapeok="t" o:connecttype="rect"/>
 <o:lock v:ext="edit" aspectratio="t"/>
</v:shapetype><v:shape id="_x0000_i1042" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:495.75pt;
 height:87.75pt' filled="t">
 <v:fill color2="black"/>
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./e_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
 <v:textbox inset="0,0,0,0"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=661 height=117
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./e_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1042"><![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<h3><span style='font-size:28.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt'>Problem E<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:20.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt;font-family:
Arial'>Configurations </span></b><span style='font-family:Arial'><br>
<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Input: </b><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>Standard Input<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Output: </span></b><span
style='font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Standard Output</span><b><span
style='font-size:20.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:1.0in;text-indent:.5in'><b><span
style='font-size:18.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:115%;mso-pagination:
none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span lang=EN
style='mso-ansi-language:EN'>Well, in this problem you are given an RxC<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>grid (1</span>&#8804;<span lang=EN
style='mso-ansi-language:EN'>R</span>&#8804;<span lang=EN style='mso-ansi-language:
EN'>10<sup>9</sup> and 1</span>&#8804;<span lang=EN style='mso-ansi-language:
EN'>C</span>&#8804;<span lang=EN style='mso-ansi-language:EN'>10). There will
be B blocks (1</span>&#8804;<span lang=EN style='mso-ansi-language:EN'>B</span>&#8804;<span
lang=EN style='mso-ansi-language:EN'>100) in the grid. Each block will be
placed in a cell of the grid. There can be more than one blocks in a cell.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:115%;mso-pagination:
none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span lang=EN
style='mso-ansi-language:EN'>Now you are given M identical tokens and you can
place them in the first row as you like. A cell cannot contain more than one
token and you also cannot place a token in a cell occupied by blocks. Now you
can move a token but you have to follow following rules:<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">               </span><br>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">        </span>1. If there is a token in a cell
(r,c) then you can move it to either (r+1,c-1) or (r+1,c+1).<br>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">        </span>2. You cannot move a token to a
cell occupied by blocks.<br>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">        </span>3. You cannot move a token
outside of the grid.<br>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">        </span>4. You cannot move two or more
tokens to the same cell.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">     </span><br>
</span><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">        </span>5. All the tokens should
be moved to i-th row before any token can be moved (i + 1)-th row. <span
lang=EN style='mso-ansi-language:EN'><span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">           </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:115%;mso-pagination:
none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span lang=EN
style='mso-ansi-language:EN'>Now let S = {(1,c<sub>1</sub>),(1,c<sub>2</sub>),...,(1,c<sub>M</sub>))
be the set of cells of where you placed M identical tokens and W(S) = number of
ways you can move these tokens to last row. You have to find the sum of W for
every possible S.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:115%;mso-pagination:
none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span lang=EN
style='mso-ansi-language:EN'>For R = 2, C = 2, M = 1 and B = 0 the answer is 2.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:115%;mso-pagination:
none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span lang=EN
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;
mso-ansi-language:EN'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id="_x0000_i1043" type="#_x0000_t75"
 style='width:240pt;height:2in'>
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./e_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=320 height=192
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./e_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1043"><![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoCaption><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial;
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";font-style:normal'>Input <o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='text-align:justify'><span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">           </span>First line contains number of test cases
1&#8804;T&#8804;500.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">   </span>For each test
case, the first line contains 1&#8804;R&#8804;10<sup>9</sup> ,
1&#8804;C&#8804;10 and<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>0&#8804;M&#8804;C respectively. The second line contains
0&#8804;B&#8804;100, followed by B lines and each of those B lines contains two
integers r and c, (1&#8804;r&#8804;R and 1&#8804;c&#8804;C) indicating the cell
position of each block.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:10.0pt;text-align:justify;line-height:
115%;mso-pagination:none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><b><span
lang=EN style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;
mso-ansi-language:EN'>Output</span></b><span lang=EN style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-ansi-language:EN'><br>
<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">          </span></span><span lang=EN
style='mso-ansi-language:EN'><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">   </span>For each
test cases you have to output the answer in a single line as shown in the
sample output. As the answer can be very large you have to mod the output with
12345.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-bottom:10.0pt;line-height:115%;mso-pagination:
none;mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span lang=EN
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Courier New";mso-ansi-language:EN'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in'><b><span lang=EN style='font-size:20.0pt;mso-ansi-language:
EN'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

 border-collapse:collapse;mso-padding-alt:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>

<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;page-break-before:
always'><b><span style='font-size:20.0pt'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id="_x0000_t75"
 coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t" path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe"
 filled="f" stroked="f">
 <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
 <v:formulas>
  <v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @6 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @8 21600 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"/>
 </v:formulas>
 <v:path o:extrusionok="f" gradientshapeok="t" o:connecttype="rect"/>
 <o:lock v:ext="edit" aspectratio="t"/>
</v:shapetype><v:shape id="_x0000_i1025" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:495.75pt;
 height:88.5pt' filled="t">
 <v:fill color2="black"/>
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./f_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
 <v:textbox inset="0,0,0,0"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=661 height=118
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./f_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1025"><![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<h3><span style='font-size:28.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt'>Problem F<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:20.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt;font-family:
Arial'>Two Longest Paths </span></b><span style='font-family:Arial'><br>
<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Input: </b><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>Standard Input<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Output: </span></b><span
style='font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Standard Output</span><b><span
style='font-size:20.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;text-align:justify;
mso-hyphenate:auto'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:
Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>Tekuhp is a tourist city. There are <i>N</i>
intersections in the city, connected with <i>M</i> one-way roads. Each one-way
road connects from some intersection to another. There maybe many roads that
connect a pair of intersections. To make the city very amazing, the roads are
constructed so that it is <b><i><u>not possible</u></i></b> to start at some
intersection, travel along the roads, and return to the starting intersection.
(It remains a strange secret how people of Tekuhp return home from work each
day.)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;text-align:justify;
mso-hyphenate:auto'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:
Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>There are two groups of tourists planning to
visit the city. They want to travel along the roads from some intersection to
another. However, both groups do not want to run into each other. So they want
two paths <i>P</i><sub>1</sub> and <i>P</i><sub>2</sub>, each <i>P<sub>i</sub></i>
, for 1 &lt;= <i>i</i> &lt;= 2, starts at some intersection <i>s<sub>i</sub></i>
and ends at intersection <i>t<sub>i</sub></i>, such that both paths share <b><i><u>no
intersections</u></i></b>, including the starting and the ending intersections.
However, it is possible that a path <i>P<sub>i</sub></i> may contain only one
node, i. e., <i>s<sub>i</sub></i> = <i>t<sub>i</sub></i>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;text-align:justify;
mso-hyphenate:auto'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:
Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>Tourists also want to visit many places.
Since you are a good planner, you want to maximize the total number of intersections
in both path.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;text-align:justify;
mso-hyphenate:auto'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:
Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial;
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt'><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">           </span>First line of the
input contains an integer T (1 &lt;= T &lt;= 10), the number of test cases.
After that T test cases follow.</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>Each test case
starts with integers <i>N</i> and <i>M</i> (1 &lt;= <i>N</i> &lt;= 300; 1 &lt;=
<i>M</i> &lt;= 3,000), where <i>N</i> denotes the number of intersections and <i>M</i>
denotes the number of roads. The intersections are numbered from 1 to <i>N</i>.
After that <i>M</i> lines, describing road connection, follow. Each line
contains two integers <i>A</i> and <i>B</i> denoting that there is a one-way
road from intersection <i>A</i> to intersection <i>B</i></span><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:EN-US'>.</span><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;mso-fareast-language:
EN-US'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;
font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;
font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Output<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText3><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt'><span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">         </span>The output must contain T lines, each
line for each test case. For each test case, the output contains an integer L
denoting the maximum number of intersections in two non-intersecting paths.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<table border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 style='border-collapse:collapse;
 border:none;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>

  </td>

<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal style='page-break-before:always'><b><span style='font-size:
20.0pt'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id="_x0000_t75" coordsize="21600,21600"
 o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t" path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" filled="f"
 stroked="f">
 <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
 <v:formulas>
  <v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @6 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @8 21600 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"/>
 </v:formulas>
 <v:path o:extrusionok="f" gradientshapeok="t" o:connecttype="rect"/>
 <o:lock v:ext="edit" aspectratio="t"/>
</v:shapetype><v:shape id="_x0000_i1047" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:495.75pt;
 height:87.75pt' filled="t">
 <v:fill color2="black"/>
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./g_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
 <v:textbox inset="0,0,0,0"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=661 height=117
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./g_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1047"><![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<h3><span style='font-size:28.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt'>Problem G<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:20.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt;font-family:
Arial'>A Minimum Land Price </span></b><span style='font-family:Arial'><br>
<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Input: </b><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>Standard Input<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Output: </span></b><span
style='font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Standard Output</span><b><span
style='font-size:20.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt'>Manager of ACM-ICPC Thailand Contest Council is planning to buy lands
in Phuket to build the office building for national programming skill camp and
programming contest that will be held on Phuket regularly in the future. The
land price in Phuket is becoming more expensive in every year. The price
increases in the exponential growth curves by a factor of year.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>If the land <b><i>i</i></b> whose initial
cost is L<sub>i</sub> bought in <b><i>t</i></b> years from now, its price will
be 2x (L<sub>i</sub>)<sup>t</sup>. All land prices are different.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>ACM-ICPC can buy only one land per year. You
have to help the manager to buy the lands at lowest price within the budget of <span
style='color:black'>5,000,000</span> millions baht.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt'>For example, if we want to buy 3 lands with costs 7 2 and 10 in 3
consecutive years, the total price will be calculated as follow.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:.5in'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt'><span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span><span style='mso-tab-count:
1'>           </span><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">    </span>(2x 7)<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>+ (2x 2<sup>2</sup>) + (2 x 10<sup>3</sup>)
= 2022 millions baht<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:11.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial;
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">           </span>First line of the input contains an integer T (1 &lt;= T
&lt;= 10), the number of test cases<span style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:
Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>. </span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt'>Each test case contain</span><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'>s integer </span>L<sub>i </sub><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'>which is the cost
of land in million baht. There are less than 40 lands in each test case. The
line contains 0 (zero) indicates the end of each test case.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial;
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Output<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>For each test case, print
out the minimum price for purchasing all lands. If the total price exceeds the
budget (<span style='color:black'>5,000,000</span> millions baht), print out
Too expensive.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:
"Angsana New"'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 style='margin-left:-5.0pt;
 border-collapse:collapse;mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
 <tr>
  <td width=284 valign=top style='width:213.1pt;border:solid black .5pt;
  border-right:none;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:20.0pt;
  font-family:Arial'>Sample Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width=298 valign=top style='width:223.15pt;border:solid black .5pt;
  padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:20.0pt;
  font-family:Arial'>Output for Sample Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td width=284 valign=top style='width:213.1pt;border-top:none;border-left:
  solid black .5pt;border-bottom:solid black .5pt;border-right:none;mso-border-top-alt:
  solid black .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;line-height:11.0pt;layout-grid-mode:

<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:20.0pt'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype
 id="_x0000_t75" coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t"
 path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" filled="f" stroked="f">
 <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
 <v:formulas>
  <v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @6 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @8 21600 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"/>
 </v:formulas>
 <v:path o:extrusionok="f" gradientshapeok="t" o:connecttype="rect"/>
 <o:lock v:ext="edit" aspectratio="t"/>
</v:shapetype><v:shape id="_x0000_i1049" type="#_x0000_t75" style='width:495.75pt;
 height:81.75pt' filled="t">
 <v:fill color2="black"/>
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./h_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
 <v:textbox inset="0,0,0,0"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=661 height=109
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./h_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1049"><![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<h3><span style='font-size:28.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt'>Problem H<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:20.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt;font-family:
Arial'>Hackers Crackdown </span></b><span style='font-family:Arial'><br>
<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Input: </b><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>Standard Input<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Output: </span></b><span
style='font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Standard Output</span><b><span
style='font-size:20.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b><span
style='font-size:20.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-line-height-alt:11.0pt'>Miracle
Corporations has a number of system services running in a distributed computer system
which is a prime target for hackers. The system is basically a set of <b>N </b>computer
nodes with each of them running a set of <b>N </b>services. Note that, the set
of services running on every node is same everywhere in the network. A hacker
can destroy a service by running a specialized exploit for that service in all
the nodes. </p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-line-height-alt:11.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-line-height-alt:11.0pt'>One
day, a smart hacker collects necessary exploits for all these <b>N </b>services
and launches an attack on the system. He finds a security hole that gives him
just enough time to run a single exploit in each computer. These exploits have
the characteristic that, its successfully infects the computer where it was
originally run and all the neighbor computers of that node. </p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-line-height-alt:11.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-line-height-alt:11.0pt'>Given
a network description, find the maximum number of services that the hacker can
damage.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-line-height-alt:11.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-line-height-alt:11.0pt'><b><span
style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in;mso-line-height-alt:
11.0pt'>There will be multiple test cases in the input file. A test case begins
with an integer <b>N (1&lt;=N&lt;=16)</b>, the number of nodes in the network.
The nodes are denoted by 0 to <b>N - 1. </b>Each of the following <b>N </b>lines
describes the neighbors of a node. Line <b>i (0&lt;=i&lt;N)</b> represents the
description of node <b>i</b>. The description for node <b>i </b>starts with an
integer <b>m </b><b><span style='font-size:11.0pt'>(</span></b>Number of
neighbors for node <b>i</b>), followed by <b>m </b>integers in the range of <b>0
</b>to <b>N - 1</b>, each denoting a neighboring node of node <b>i</b>.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-line-height-alt:11.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-line-height-alt:11.0pt'>The
end of input will be denoted by a case with <b>N = 0</b>. This case should not
be processed. </p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-line-height-alt:11.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-line-height-alt:11.0pt'><b><span
style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Output<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in;mso-line-height-alt:
11.0pt'>For each test case, print a line in the format, <b>Case X: Y</b>,
where <b>X</b> is the case number &amp; <b>Y</b> is the maximum possible number
of services that can be damaged. </p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;mso-line-height-alt:11.0pt'><b><span
style='mso-tab-count:4'>                                                </span><span
style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span><o:p></o:p></b></p>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 style='margin-left:-5.0pt;
 border-collapse:collapse;mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
 <tr>
  <td width=314 valign=top style='width:235.4pt;border:solid black .5pt;
  border-right:none;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:20.0pt;
  font-family:Arial'>Sample Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width=330 valign=top style='width:247.5pt;border:solid black .5pt;
  padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:20.0pt;
  font-family:Arial'>Output for Sample Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td width=314 valign=top style='width:235.4pt;border-top:none;border-left:
  solid black .5pt;border-bottom:solid black .5pt;border-right:none;mso-border-top-alt:

<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal style='page-break-before:always'><b><span style='font-size:
20.0pt'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype id="_x0000_t75" coordsize="21600,21600"
 o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t" path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" filled="f"

  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>

  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"/>

</v:shapetype><v:shape id="Picture_x0020_33" o:spid="_x0000_i1051" type="#_x0000_t75"
 alt="logoACM-horiz-I" style='width:495.75pt;height:78.75pt;visibility:visible'>

src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./i_files/image001.png"  alt=logoACM-horiz-I v:shapes="Picture_x0020_33"><![endif]></span></b><b><span
style='font-size:17.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<h3><span style='font-size:28.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt'>Problem I<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:20.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:24.0pt;font-family:
Arial'>Shuffle </span></b><span style='font-family:Arial'><br>
<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Input: </b><span style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
bold'>Standard Input<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Output: </span></b><span
style='font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Standard Output</span><b><span
style='font-size:20.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b><span
style='font-size:16.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>My office is quite far from my
home. Every day, I go there by bus. That takes a lot of time. More over, due to
traffic jams, the time to reach my office is not fixed. To make the best use of
this time, I carry my music player all the time.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>My music player has a shuffle
mode. In that mode, the music player selects a track randomly that has not been
played in that session, and starts playing. It will continue doing so, until, I
have stopped playing, or it has played all tracks in that session. For the
purpose of this problem, you can assume that all tracks are of equal duration.
To select randomly, the player keeps list of the tracks already played. That
is, if I listen to one track now, from next shuffle session, that track will be
marked as played. To select a random track, the player always use such strategy
that, selecting an old track (Already listened) is twice more probable than a
new track (Not listened).</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>I go to my office in the morning
and return home at night. It takes at least p minutes and at most q minutes to
reach my office. The time required will always be an integer. You can assume
that all travel times are equiprobable (that is, if p = 2 and q = 4, and if
P(t) is the probability to reach office in t minutes, then P(2) = P(3) = P(4)).
If all tracks are of 1 minute, how many days on average are required to listen
to all the songs?</p>

<h2 style='margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;margin-left:
.4in;text-indent:-.4in;mso-pagination:none;page-break-after:avoid;tab-stops:
list .4in'><span style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial'>Input<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

<p class=MsoNormal>First line of input contains an integer <b>T(&#8804;10053)</b>,
the number of test cases.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Each test case contains 5 integers, <b>N
(1&#8804;N&#8804;75)</b>, <b>p<sub><span style='mso-font-kerning:12.0pt'>1</span></sub>,
q<sub>1</sub>, p<sub>2</sub>, q<sub>2 </sub>(0 &#8804; p<sub>1</sub>, q<sub>1</sub>,
p<sub>2</sub>, q<sub>2 </sub>&#8804; 30, p<sub>1 </sub>&#8804; q<sub>1</sub>, p<sub>2
</sub>&#8804; q<sub>2</sub>)</b>, where <b>N</b> is the number of songs, <b>p<sub>1</sub>,q<sub>1</sub></b>
are the minimum and maximum number of songs listened during day, and <b>p<sub>2</sub>,q<sub>2</sub></b>
are the minimum and maximum number of songs during night.</p>

<h2 style='margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt;margin-left:
.4in;text-indent:-.4in;mso-pagination:none;page-break-after:avoid;tab-stops:
list .4in'><span style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial'>Output<o:p></o:p></span></h2>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='text-align:justify'><span style='mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman"'>For each test case, output the test case, followed by the
expected number of days required to listen all songs. If its not possible to
listen to all songs, output </span><span style='font-family:"Courier New";
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>IMPOSSIBLE</span><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>. Errors less than 10<sup>-6</sup>
will be tolerated.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=665 style='width:498.6pt;
 margin-left:2.75pt;border-collapse:collapse;mso-padding-alt:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
