<body lang=EN-US style='tab-interval:.5in'>

<div class=Section1>

<div align=center>

<table border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 style='border-collapse:collapse;
 border:none;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .25pt;mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
 <tr>
  <td width=97 valign=top style='width:73.1pt;border:solid windowtext .25pt;
  background:#E6E6E6;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><b
  style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:60.0pt;font-family:
  Arial'>G<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width=446 valign=top style='width:4.65in;border:solid windowtext .25pt;
  border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .25pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><span
  style='font-size:28.0pt;font-family:Impact;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial'>Stream
  My Contest<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><b
  style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Input:</span></b><span
  style='font-family:Arial'> Standard Input<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><b
  style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Output:</span></b><span
  style='font-family:Arial'> Standard Output<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width=101 valign=top style='width:75.4pt;border:solid windowtext .25pt;
  border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .25pt;background:#E0E0E0;
  padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype
   id="_x0000_t75" coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t"
   path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" filled="f" stroked="f">
   <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>

   <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./g_files/image001.png"  o:href="http://www.informatik.uni-ulm.de/acm/images/acmlogo.gif"/>
  </v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=86 height=85
  src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./g_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1025"><![endif]></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

</div>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='text-align:justify;line-height:115%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'>During 2009 and
2010 ICPC world finals, the contest was webcasted via world wide web. Seeing
this, some contest organizers from <i>Ajobdesh</i> decided that, they will
provide a live stream of their contests to every university in <i>Ajobdesh</i>.
The organizers have decided that, they will provide best possible service to
them. But there are two problems:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='text-align:justify;line-height:115%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='text-align:justify;line-height:115%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'>1. There is no
existing network between universities. So, they need to build a new network.
However, the maximum amount they can spend on building the network is <b><i>C</i></b>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='text-align:justify;line-height:115%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'>2. Each link in
the network has a bandwidth. If, the streams bandwidth exceeds any of the
links available bandwidth, the viewers, connected through that link cant view
the stream.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='text-align:justify;line-height:115%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='text-align:justify;line-height:115%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'>Due to the
protocols used for streaming, a viewer can receive stream from exactly one
other user (or the server, where the contest is organized). That is, if you
have two 128kbps links, you wont get 256kbps bandwidth, although, if you have
a stream of 128kbps, you can stream to any number of users at that bandwidth.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='text-align:justify;line-height:115%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial'>Given C,
you have to maximize the minimum bandwidth to any user.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial;
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='text-align:justify;line-height:115%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'>First line of
input contains <b><i>T(&#8804;50)</i></b>, the number of test cases. This is
followed by <b><i>T</i></b> test cases.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='text-align:justify;line-height:115%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='text-align:justify;line-height:115%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'>Each test case
starts with an integer <b><i>N,M,C</i>(1&#8804;N&#8804;60,1&#8804;M&#8804;10<sup>4,</sup>1&#8804;C&#8804;10<sup>9</sup>)</b>,
the number of universities and the number of possible links, and the budget for
setting up the network. Each university is identified by an integer between 0
and <b><i>N</i></b>-1, where 0 is the server.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='text-align:justify;line-height:115%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='text-align:justify;line-height:115%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'>Next M lines
each contain 4 integers, <b><i>u,v,b,c</i>(0&#8804;u, v&lt;N, 1&#8804;b,
c&#8804;10<sup>6</sup>, u!=v)</b>, describing a possible link from university <b><i>u</i></b>
to university <b><i>v</i></b>, that has the bandwidth of <b><i>b</i></b> kbps
and of cost <b><i>c</i></b>. All links are unidirectional.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='text-align:justify;line-height:115%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='text-align:justify;line-height:115%'><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'>There is a blank
line before each test case.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;font-family:Arial;
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Output<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=Style-2 style='line-height:115%'><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'>For each test case, output the maximum
bandwidth to stream. If its not possible, output </span><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Courier New";
color:black'></span><span style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Courier New";mso-fareast-font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>streaming
not possible.</span><span style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Courier New";color:black'></span><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;color:black'>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoHeader style='tab-stops:.5in center 3.0in right 6.0in'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<h1 align=left style='text-align:left'><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal'>Sample
Input<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">                              
</span>Output for Sample Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></h1>

<div class=Section1>

<div align=center>

<table border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 style='border-collapse:collapse;

 <tr>
  <td width=97 valign=top style='width:73.1pt;border:solid windowtext .25pt;
  background:#E6E6E6;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><b
  style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:60.0pt;font-family:
  Arial'>H<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width=446 valign=top style='width:4.65in;border:solid windowtext .25pt;
  border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .25pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><span
  style='font-size:28.0pt;font-family:Impact;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial'>Triangle<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><b
  style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Input:</span></b><span
  style='font-family:Arial'> Standard Input<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><b
  style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Output:</span></b><span
  style='font-family:Arial'> Standard Output<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width=101 valign=top style='width:75.4pt;border:solid windowtext .25pt;
  border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .25pt;background:#E0E0E0;
  padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype
   id="_x0000_t75" coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t"
   path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" filled="f" stroked="f">
   <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
   <v:formulas>
    <v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"/>
    <v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"/>
    <v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"/>
    <v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"/>
    <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"/>
    <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>
    <v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"/>
    <v:f eqn="prod @6 1 2"/>
    <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"/>
    <v:f eqn="sum @8 21600 0"/>
    <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>
    <v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"/>
   </v:formulas>
   <v:path o:extrusionok="f" gradientshapeok="t" o:connecttype="rect"/>
   <o:lock v:ext="edit" aspectratio="t"/>
  </v:shapetype><v:shape id="_x0000_i1025" type="#_x0000_t75" alt="  style='width:64.5pt;
   height:63.75pt'>
   <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./h_files/image001.png"  o:href="http://www.informatik.uni-ulm.de/acm/images/acmlogo.gif"/>
  </v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=86 height=85
  src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./h_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1025"><![endif]></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

</div>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='text-align:justify'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Verdana;mso-bidi-font-family:Verdana;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h1><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;
font-style:normal'>How many triangles are there when they have integer length
sides and all the sides are between X and Y inclusive. Two triangles differs if
their side length set s are different. For example {2,3,3}, {2,3,4} and {2,2,3}
are all different triangles. But {5,6,7} and {6,5,7} are not different. In a
triangle the sum of smaller two sides are strictly greater than the largest
side.<o:p></o:p></span></h1>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<h5 style='text-align:justify'><span class=StyleArial16pt><span
style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial'>Input</span></span><span
class=StyleArial16pt><span style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial;mso-fareast-font-family:"Arial Unicode MS"'><o:p></o:p></span></span></h5>

<p class=MsoBodyText2><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'>Input starts with an integer T(1 &#8804; T &#8804; 20000), the number
of test cases. Each test case consists of two integer X and Y(1 &#8804; X
&#8804; Y &#8804; 1000000).<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<h4><span class=StyleArial16pt><span style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:
10.0pt;font-family:Arial'>Output <o:p></o:p></span></span></h4>

<p class=MsoBodyText2><span style='mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'>For each test case, output the number of possible triangles whose side
lengths are between X and Y inclusive.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<h1 align=left style='text-align:left'><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal'>Sample
Input<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">                              
</span>Output for Sample Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></h1>

<table border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 bgcolor="#cccccc" style='background:
 #CCCCCC;border-collapse:collapse;border:none;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;
 mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
 <tr style='height:13.9pt'>
  <td width=319 valign=top style='width:239.4pt;border:solid windowtext .5pt;
  padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;height:13.9pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal style='mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span

  <p class=MsoNormal style='mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span
  style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'>1
  10<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=MsoNormal style='mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span
  style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'>5

  <p class=MsoNormal style='mso-layout-grid-align:none;text-autospace:none'><span

  <p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-bottom:14.15pt'><span style='font-size:

<div class=Section1>

<div align=center>

<table border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 style='border-collapse:collapse;
 border:none;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .25pt;mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
 <tr>
  <td width=97 valign=top style='width:73.1pt;border:solid windowtext .25pt;
  background:#E6E6E6;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><b
  style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:60.0pt;font-family:
  Arial'>I<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width=446 valign=top style='width:4.65in;border:solid windowtext .25pt;
  border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .25pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><span
  style='font-size:28.0pt;font-family:Impact;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial'>Politeness<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><b
  style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Input:</span></b><span
  style='font-family:Arial'> Standard Input<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><b
  style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:Arial'>Output:</span></b><span
  style='font-family:Arial'> Standard Output<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width=101 valign=top style='width:75.4pt;border:solid windowtext .25pt;
  border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .25pt;background:#E0E0E0;
  padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:143.25pt'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype
   id="_x0000_t75" coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t"
   path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" filled="f" stroked="f">
   <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
   <v:formulas>
    <v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"/>
    <v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"/>
    <v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"/>
    <v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"/>
    <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"/>
    <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>
    <v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"/>
    <v:f eqn="prod @6 1 2"/>
    <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"/>
    <v:f eqn="sum @8 21600 0"/>
    <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>
    <v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"/>
   </v:formulas>
   <v:path o:extrusionok="f" gradientshapeok="t" o:connecttype="rect"/>
   <o:lock v:ext="edit" aspectratio="t"/>
  </v:shapetype><v:shape id="_x0000_i1025" type="#_x0000_t75" alt="  style='width:64.5pt;
   height:63.75pt'>
   <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./i_files/image001.png"  o:href="http://www.informatik.uni-ulm.de/acm/images/acmlogo.gif"/>
  </v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=86 height=85
  src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./i_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_i1025"><![endif]></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

</div>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>A number is called polite if it
can be written as a sum of some consecutive positive integer. For example, 6 (1+2+3)
is a polite number while 4 is not. Politeness of a number is the number of ways
it can be expressed as sum of consecutive positive integer. For example
6(1+2+3) is a politeness of 1 while 18(5+6+7 = 3+4+5+6) has a politeness of 2.
Obviously, non polite number has a politeness of 0. </p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>You are given a politeness P, you
have to find out the smallest number that has the politeness P.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Verdana'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h5 style='text-align:justify'><span class=StyleArial16pt><span
style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial'>Input</span></span><span
class=StyleArial16pt><span style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial;mso-fareast-font-family:"Arial Unicode MS"'><o:p></o:p></span></span></h5>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>The first line of input will
indicate the number of test cases T (T &lt;= 1000). Each of the following T
lines will contain a non negative integer number P (P &lt; 10^12) indicating
the desired politeness.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></b></p>

<h5 style='text-align:justify'><span class=StyleArial16pt><span
style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial'>Output</span></span><span
class=StyleArial16pt><span style='font-size:16.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial;mso-fareast-font-family:"Arial Unicode MS"'><o:p></o:p></span></span></h5>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'>For each line of input you have
to produce one line of output that will contain number that has a politeness of
P. If there is more than one number having that politeness choose the smallest
one. If there is no such number print impossible. If the number is greater than
1000000007 print the number mod 1000000007.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<h1 align=left style='text-align:left'><b><span style='font-size:16.0pt;
mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal'>Sample
Input<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">                                
</span>Output for Sample Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></h1>

<table border=1 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 bgcolor="#cccccc" style='background:
 #CCCCCC;border-collapse:collapse;border:none;mso-border-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;
 mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
 <tr>
  <td width=331 valign=top style='width:3.45in;border:solid windowtext .5pt;
  padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
  mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'>3<br>
  0<br>
  1<br>
  5<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><span
  style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width=343 valign=top style='width:257.05pt;border:solid windowtext .5pt;
  border-left:none;mso-border-left-alt:solid windowtext .5pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal><span style='font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;
  font-family:"Courier New"'>1<br>
  3<br>
  45<br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
  <![if !supportLineBreakNewLine]><br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
  <![endif]></span><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
  style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Courier New"'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
 </tr>

</table>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>John decided to
buy his son Johnny some mathematical toys. One of his most favorite toy is blocks
of different colors. John has decided to buy blocks of <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span lang=EN-ZA style='font-family:"Courier New";mso-ansi-language:
EN-ZA'>C</span></b>&nbsp;different colors. For each color he will buy googol (<span
lang=EN-ZA style='mso-ansi-language:EN-ZA'>10<sup>100</sup></span>) blocks. All
blocks of same color are of same length. But blocks of different color may vary
in length.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>Jhonny has
decided to use these blocks to make a large <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span lang=EN-ZA style='font-family:"Courier New";mso-ansi-language:
EN-ZA'>1 x n</span></b> block. He wonders how many ways he can do this. Two
ways are considered different if there is a position where the color differs.
The example shows a red block of size 5, blue block of size 3 and green block
of size 3. It shows there are 12 ways of making a large block of length 11.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 style='margin-left:16.55pt;
 border-collapse:collapse;mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
 <tr>
  <td width=326 valign=top style='width:244.35pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><!--[if gte vml 1]><o:wrapblock><v:shapetype
    id="_x0000_t75" coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t"
    path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" filled="f" stroked="f">
    <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
    <v:formulas>
     <v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"/>
     <v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"/>
     <v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"/>
     <v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"/>
     <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"/>
     <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>
     <v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"/>
     <v:f eqn="prod @6 1 2"/>
     <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"/>
     <v:f eqn="sum @8 21600 0"/>
     <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>
     <v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"/>
    </v:formulas>
    <v:path o:extrusionok="f" gradientshapeok="t" o:connecttype="rect"/>
    <o:lock v:ext="edit" aspectratio="t"/>
   </v:shapetype><v:shape id="_x0000_s1036" type="#_x0000_t75" style='position:absolute;
    left:0;text-align:left;margin-left:.5pt;margin-top:-170.75pt;width:172.45pt;
    height:147.3pt;z-index:1;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;
    mso-position-vertical-relative:text'>
    <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./a_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
    <w:wrap type="topAndBottom" anchorx="page"/>
   </v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><span style='mso-ignore:vglayout'>
   <table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
    <tr>
     <td width=1 height=0></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td></td>
     <td><img width=230 height=197 src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./a_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_s1036"></td>
    </tr>
   </table>
   </span><![endif]><!--[if gte vml 1]></o:wrapblock><![endif]--><br
  style='mso-ignore:vglayout' clear=ALL>
  </p>
  </td>
  <td width=326 valign=top style='width:244.35pt;padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt'>
  <p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><!--[if gte vml 1]><o:wrapblock><v:shape
    id="_x0000_s1037" type="#_x0000_t75" style='position:absolute;left:0;
    text-align:left;margin-left:.7pt;margin-top:-163.25pt;width:189.1pt;
    height:154.45pt;z-index:2;mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;
    mso-position-vertical-relative:text'>
    <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./a_files/image001.png"  o:title=" />
    <w:wrap type="topAndBottom" anchorx="page"/>
   </v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><span style='mso-ignore:vglayout'>
   <table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
    <tr>
     <td width=1 height=0></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td></td>
     <td><img width=252 height=206 src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./a_files/image001.png"  v:shapes="_x0000_s1037"></td>
    </tr>
   </table>
   </span><![endif]><!--[if gte vml 1]></o:wrapblock><![endif]--><br
  style='mso-ignore:vglayout' clear=ALL>
  </p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

<h2 style='margin-top:6.0pt'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-size:14.0pt'>Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></h2>

<h2 style='margin-top:6.0pt'>Input starts with a positive integer <b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=EN-ZA style='font-family:"Courier New";
mso-ansi-language:EN-ZA'>T &#8804; 25</span></b>. <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span lang=EN-ZA style='font-family:"Courier New";mso-ansi-language:
EN-ZA'>T</span></b>&nbsp;test cases follow.</h2>

<h2 style='margin-top:6.0pt'>Each test case starts with an integer <b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>1 </span></b><b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=EN-ZA style='font-family:"Courier New";
mso-ansi-language:EN-ZA'>&#8804; C &#8804; 100</span></b>. Next line consists c
integers. <span lang=EN-ZA style='mso-ansi-language:EN-ZA'>i</span>th
integer&nbsp;<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:
"Courier New"'>1 </span></b><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
lang=EN-ZA style='font-family:"Courier New";mso-ansi-language:EN-ZA'>&#8804;
len<sub>i</sub> &#8804; 750</span></b><span lang=EN-ZA> </span>denotes length
of <span lang=EN-ZA style='mso-ansi-language:EN-ZA'>i</span><sup>th</sup>
color. Next line is positive integer <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
lang=EN-ZA style='font-family:"Courier New";mso-ansi-language:EN-ZA'>n &#8804;
10<sup>15</sup></span></b>.</h2>

<h2 style='margin-top:6.0pt'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-size:14.0pt'>Output<o:p></o:p></span></b></h2>

<h2 style='margin-top:6.0pt'>For each case output case number followed by the
number of ways Johnny can make the desired block modulo 100000007 (a prime
number). See sample output for exact format.<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:14.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></h2>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><br
style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
<![if !supportLineBreakNewLine]><br style='mso-special-character:line-break'>
<![endif]><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Liberation Serif";
mso-fareast-font-family:"DejaVu Sans";mso-hansi-font-family:"Liberation Serif";
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=665 style='width:498.7pt;
 margin-left:2.75pt;border-collapse:collapse;mso-padding-alt:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>

	text-indent:-.25in;}
@list l0:level9
	{mso-level-tab-stop:2.5in;
	mso-level-number-position:left;
	margin-left:2.5in;
	text-indent:-.25in;}
@list l1
	{mso-list-id:1819881313;
	mso-list-type:hybrid;
	mso-list-template-ids:1809755552 348153884 67698713 67698715 67698703 67698713 67698715 67698703 67698713 67698715;}
@list l1:level1
	{mso-level-number-format:roman-lower;
	mso-level-text:"%1\)";
	mso-level-tab-stop:none;
	mso-level-number-position:left;
	margin-left:.75in;
	text-indent:-.5in;}
ol
	{margin-bottom:0in;}
ul
	{margin-bottom:0in;}
-->
</style>
<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>
 <o:shapedefaults v:ext="edit" spidmax="12290"/>
</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>
 <o:shapelayout v:ext="edit">
  <o:idmap v:ext="edit" data="1"/>
 </o:shapelayout></xml><![endif]-->
</head>

<body lang=EN-US style='tab-interval:.5in'>

<div class=Section1>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 style='margin-left:2.55pt;
 border-collapse:collapse;mso-padding-alt:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
 <tr style='height:59.05pt'>
  <td width=90 rowspan=3 style='width:67.55pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  border-right:none;padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt;height:59.05pt'>
  <p class=TableContents align=center style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:center;
  layout-grid-mode:char'><b><span style='font-size:72.0pt'>B</span></b><b><span
  style='font-size:72.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width=573 colspan=2 style='width:429.85pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt;height:59.05pt'>
  <p class=TableContents align=center style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:center;
  layout-grid-mode:char'><span style='font-size:36.0pt'>SOAP Response</span><span
  style='font-size:36.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr style='height:18.55pt'>
  <td width=278 valign=top style='width:208.45pt;border-top:none;border-left:
  solid black .25pt;border-bottom:solid black .25pt;border-right:none;
  padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt;height:18.55pt'>
  <p class=TableContents align=right style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:right;
  layout-grid-mode:char'><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>Input</span><span
  style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width=295 valign=top style='width:221.4pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  border-top:none;padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt;height:18.55pt'>
  <p class=TableContents style='margin-top:6.0pt;layout-grid-mode:char'><span
  style='font-size:10.0pt'>Standard Input</span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
  mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr style='height:1.15pt'>
  <td width=278 valign=top style='width:208.45pt;border-top:none;border-left:
  solid black .25pt;border-bottom:solid black .25pt;border-right:none;
  padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt;height:1.15pt'>
  <p class=TableContents align=right style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:right;
  layout-grid-mode:char'><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>Output</span><span
  style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width=295 valign=top style='width:221.4pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  border-top:none;padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt;height:1.15pt'>
  <p class=TableContents style='margin-top:6.0pt;layout-grid-mode:char'><span
  style='font-size:10.0pt'>Standard Output</span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
  mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype
 id="_x0000_t75" coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t"
 path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" filled="f" stroked="f">
 <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
 <v:formulas>
  <v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @6 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @8 21600 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"/>
 </v:formulas>
 <v:path o:extrusionok="f" gradientshapeok="t" o:connecttype="rect"/>
 <o:lock v:ext="edit" aspectratio="t"/>
</v:shapetype><v:shape id="Picture_x0020_1" o:spid="_x0000_s1033" type="#_x0000_t75"
 alt="C:\Documents and Settings\Shamim Hafiz\Desktop\soap-mep-2.png" style='position:absolute;
 left:0;text-align:left;margin-left:0;margin-top:59.2pt;width:134.7pt;height:84.75pt;
 z-index:1;visibility:visible;mso-position-horizontal:left;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;mso-position-vertical-relative:text'>
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  o:title="soap-mep-2"/>
 <v:textbox style='mso-rotate-with-shape:t'/>
 <w:wrap type="square" anchorx="page"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=180 height=113
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./b_files/image001.png"  align=left hspace=12
alt="C:\Documents and Settings\Shamim Hafiz\Desktop\soap-mep-2.png" v:shapes="Picture_x0020_1"><![endif]>With
increasing availability of broadband internet and significant progress in Web technology,
Web Services are playing a crucial role in application development.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The basic idea behind Web Service is, the
server hosting the services can be queried and it will send back the response
based on the query. Similar to all other forms of communication, a protocol
must exist on how the messages should be communicated. One popular protocol is
SOAP(Simple Object Access Protocol). As the name suggests, it deals with
sending objects across client and server machine. Since objects are represented
differently in different languages, the objects are sent in a common text based
format known as XML. In this problem, we will be analyzing a simplified version
of SOAP messages in XML format and evaluate queries based on the message. </p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>The XML messages
will be formatted as below:</p>

<p class=ListParagraph style='margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
10.0pt;margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;
mso-hyphenate:auto'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman"'>i)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Each
line consists of either an opening tag or a closing tag.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=ListParagraph style='margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
10.0pt;margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;
mso-hyphenate:auto'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman"'>ii)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Each
tag will have a name.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=ListParagraph style='margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
10.0pt;margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;
mso-hyphenate:auto'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman"'>iii)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Each
opening tag can have zero or more properties. The properties will have a value
assigned to them. These names and values will have at least one character. The
property names in individual tags will be unique.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>See examples below for exact formatting.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=ListParagraph style='margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
10.0pt;margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;
mso-hyphenate:auto'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman"'>iv)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Closing
tags will not have any properties.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=ListParagraph style='margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
10.0pt;margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.5in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;
mso-hyphenate:auto'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:"Times New Roman"'>v)<span style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]><span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Tags
can be nested inside another tag. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt'>Example XML message and
description:<br>
<i style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>&lt;one valid=true active=alive&gt;<br>
&lt;anestedtag&gt;<br>
&lt;/anestedtag&gt;<br>
&lt;/one&gt;</i></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>In the above
example, we have a tag named one which has two properties, namely<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>valid and active.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The property named valid has a value of
true and active has a value of alive.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Each property information is separated from each other by a single space
and there is also a space after tag name if the tag has any property.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>No other space occurs in the XML text other
than those mentioned earlier. There is a tag named anestedtag which<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>is nested inside the tag named one. Note
that, this tag doesnt have any properties defined. Closing tags contain the
same name of the corresponding opening tag, but is preceded by the /
character. <i style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><o:p></o:p></i></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>You will be
given a simplified soap message, containing only start and end tags with
property information embedded in the start tag as the above format. Then you
will have some query with some property name under some tag. You need output
the value of the property under the specified tags or report such property is
undefined.<i style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'><o:p></o:p></i></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt'>Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>The first line
of input will be a positive integer <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>T </span></b><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span lang=EN-ZA style='font-family:"Courier New";mso-ansi-language:
EN-ZA'>&#8804; </span></b><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>10</span></b>, where <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>T</span></b> denotes the number
of test cases.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Each case starts with a
positive integer <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:
"Courier New"'>n </span></b><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
lang=EN-ZA style='font-family:"Courier New";mso-ansi-language:EN-ZA'>&#8804; </span></b><b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>1000</span></b>
and <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>n</span></b>
will always be even. The next <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>n</span></b> lines each describes an opening
or a closing<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>tag. These lines will have
at most <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>1000</span></b>
characters. The last line of the input will always be the closing tag for the
tag opened in the first line. No opening tag name will occur more than once.
All input will be syntactically valid, that means all opening tags will also
contain a corresponding closing tags in the appropriate line.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The next line will contain a positive
integer <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>q
&lt;= 1000</span></b>. Each of the next <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>q</span></b> lines will describe a
query.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The query will consist of tag
names separated by a dot(.) followed by few characters in the format
[&lt;prop name&gt;], where &lt;prop name&gt; is one or more character
forming a property name. See sample input for exact formatting.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>All <i
style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>names</i> and <i style='mso-bidi-font-style:
normal'>values</i> in the input will consist of alphabets only.<span
style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt'>Output</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>Each case of output
will contain the case number in one line. Then there will be <b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>q</span></b>
lines, each corresponding to the property value given in the query.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>If that particular property does not exist,
the output will be Undefined without the quotes. Note that, the input queries
will always be syntactically valid, but they may refer to tags and properties
that are not defined. If two tags are separated by a ., it indicates that the
tag to the right should be contained within the left tag.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>See sample <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'>input/output</b> for further clarification. In output, there should not
be any leading or trailing spaces in any of the line.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=665 style='width:498.7pt;
 margin-left:2.75pt;border-collapse:collapse;mso-padding-alt:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
 <tr>
  <td width=332 valign=top style='width:249.25pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  border-right:none;padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
  <p class=TableContents style='margin-top:6.0pt;layout-grid-mode:char'><b><span
  style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>Sample Input</span></b><b><span
  style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width=333 valign=top style='width:249.45pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
  <p class=TableContents style='margin-top:6.0pt;layout-grid-mode:char'><b><span
  style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>Sample Output</span></b><b><span
  style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td width=332 valign=top style='width:249.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:
  solid black .25pt;border-bottom:solid black .25pt;border-right:none;
  padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
  <p class=SampleIO style='margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
  0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>1<br>
  8<br>
  &lt;a good=&quot;true&quot; wants=&quot;no&quot;&gt;<br>
  &lt;b&gt;<br>
  &lt;c contest=&quot;running&quot;&gt;<br>
  &lt;d ballon=&quot;no&quot;&gt;<br>
  &lt;/d&gt;<br>
  &lt;/c&gt;<br>
  &lt;/b&gt;<br>
  &lt;/a&gt;<br>
  4<br>
  a.b.c.d[&quot;ballon&quot;]<br>
  a.c[&quot;contest&quot;]<br>
  a.b.c[&quot;contest&quot;]<br>
  c[&quot;contest&quot;]<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width=333 valign=top style='width:249.45pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  border-top:none;padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
  <p class=SampleIO style='margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
  0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>Case
  1:<br>
  no<br>
  Undefined<br>
  running<br>
  Undefined <o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

<style>
<!--

	mso-font-pitch:fixed;
	mso-font-signature:-1610612033 1757936891 16 0 131231 0;}

	{font-family:Tahoma;
	panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;

	mso-font-signature:1627421319 -2147483648 8 0 66047 0;}
@font-face
	{font-family:"Liberation Serif";
	mso-font-alt:"Times New Roman";
	mso-font-charset:128;
	mso-generic-font-family:roman;
	mso-font-pitch:variable;
	mso-font-signature:0 0 0 0 0 0;}
@font-face
	{font-family:"\@MS Mincho";
	panose-1:2 2 6 9 4 2 5 8 3 4;
	mso-font-charset:128;
	mso-generic-font-family:modern;

	mso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;

	mso-style-parent:" ;

<body lang=EN-US style='tab-interval:.5in'>

<div class=Section1>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 style='margin-left:2.55pt;
 border-collapse:collapse;mso-padding-alt:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
 <tr style='height:59.05pt'>
  <td width=90 rowspan=3 style='width:67.55pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  border-right:none;padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt;height:59.05pt'>
  <p class=TableContents align=center style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:center;
  layout-grid-mode:char'><b><span style='font-size:72.0pt'>C</span></b><b><span
  style='font-size:72.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width=573 colspan=2 style='width:429.85pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt;height:59.05pt'>
  <p class=TableContents align=center style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:center;
  layout-grid-mode:char'><span style='font-size:36.0pt'>Antonyms</span><span
  style='font-size:36.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr style='height:18.55pt'>
  <td width=278 valign=top style='width:208.45pt;border-top:none;border-left:
  solid black .25pt;border-bottom:solid black .25pt;border-right:none;
  padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt;height:18.55pt'>
  <p class=TableContents align=right style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:right;
  layout-grid-mode:char'><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>Input</span><span
  style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width=295 valign=top style='width:221.4pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  border-top:none;padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt;height:18.55pt'>
  <p class=TableContents style='margin-top:6.0pt;layout-grid-mode:char'><span
  style='font-size:10.0pt'>Standard Input</span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
  mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr style='height:1.15pt'>
  <td width=278 valign=top style='width:208.45pt;border-top:none;border-left:
  solid black .25pt;border-bottom:solid black .25pt;border-right:none;
  padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt;height:1.15pt'>
  <p class=TableContents align=right style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:right;
  layout-grid-mode:char'><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>Output</span><span
  style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width=295 valign=top style='width:221.4pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  border-top:none;padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt;height:1.15pt'>
  <p class=TableContents style='margin-top:6.0pt;layout-grid-mode:char'><span
  style='font-size:10.0pt'>Standard Output</span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
  mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;
margin-left:16.55pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt'><span style='font-family:"Liberation Serif";
mso-fareast-font-family:"DejaVu Sans";mso-hansi-font-family:"Liberation Serif";
mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Little Rushel is preparing for his
English test. Part of the test includes matching pairs of words as antonyms or
synonyms. A pair of words are called synonyms of each other if both words mean
the same thing. For example, big and large are synonyms. A pair of words
are called antonyms of each other if each is the opposite of the other. For
example, big and small are antonyms. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>For his test, Rushel needs to memorize a
huge list of words. This is really tedious and he would rather spend the time
learning to program. So, he comes up with a clever scheme. He notices that if
one word is a synonym of another, it is also the antonym of all words that are
antonyms of that word. This means that he needs only remember that the words
big and large are synonyms and that big and small are antonyms, and
from that he can infer that large and small are also antonyms. Thus he does
not need to memorize the relationship between all pairs of words, only enough
for him to be able to deduce the answer for the rest. Of course, not all words
are related (e.g. big and cold), but the examiner is a sensible person and
will not ask meaningless questions like that.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>After a little more thought, Rushel
observed that for a set of words that are related, the following rules apply:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
6.0pt;margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2;
tab-stops:list .5in'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>1.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><![endif]><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>If A and B are synonyms and B and C are
synonyms, A and C are synonyms.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
6.0pt;margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2;
tab-stops:list .5in'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>2.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><![endif]><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>If A and B are synonyms and B and C are
antonyms, A and C are antonyms.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
6.0pt;margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2;
tab-stops:list .5in'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>3.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><![endif]><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>If A and B are antonyms and B and C are
synonyms, A and C are antonyms.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
6.0pt;margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2;
tab-stops:list .5in'><![if !supportLists]><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>4.<span
style='font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><![endif]><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>If A and B are antonyms and B and C are
antonyms, A and C are synonyms.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Unfortunately for Rushel, his friends
pointed out that the rules are too simple for a real human language like
English. For example, if fed the data that ice and water are antonyms, and
that fire and water are also antonyms, it would lead one to infer that
ice and fire are synonyms (by Rule 4), which is obviously wrong. Rushel
thinks that this is not really a good example (after all, it doesn't make a lot
of sense), but he is still concerned that there might be equally nonsensical
relationships in the words that he is learning. He has already prepared lists
of synonyms and antonyms to learn, he thinks it will be enough to just check if
any of them contain any contradictions.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>A set of relationships is said to contain
a contradiction if some of the relationships imply or state that a certain pair
of words are synonyms while some of the other relationships imply or state that
the same pair are antonyms.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Please help Rushel, who is too young to
be allowed into this contest, by writing a program that takes as its input sets
of pairs of synonyms and antonyms and verifies that there are no contradictions
in them.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:
"Times New Roman"'>Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>The first line of the input will contain
a single integer </span><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>T</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
all by itself, </span><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>T </span></b><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span lang=EN-ZA style='font-family:"Courier New";mso-ansi-language:
EN-ZA'>&#8804; </span></b><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>100</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>.
T test cases follow.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Each test case starts with two numbers </span><b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>N</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> and </span><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>M (1 </span></b><b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=EN-ZA style='font-family:"Courier New";
mso-ansi-language:EN-ZA'>&#8804;</span></b><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'> N, M </span></b><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span lang=EN-ZA style='font-family:"Courier New";mso-ansi-language:
EN-ZA'>&#8804;</span></b><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'> 1000)</span></b><span style='font-family:
"Times New Roman"'>. </span><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>N</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
lines follow, each containing a pair of words separated by one or more spaces.
Then another </span><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>M</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
lines follow, also containing pairs of words separated by one or more spaces. Words
will be made up of lowercase English characters only ('a' to 'z'), and will
never be more than 20 characters long. The first set (the first </span><b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>N</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> pairs) is the set of synonyms and the
second set (the latter </span><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>M</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
pairs) is the set of antonyms.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Output<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>For each case output one line of the form
</span><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>Case
X: Y</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>, where </span><b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>X</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> is the test case (starting from 1) and </span><b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>Y</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> is either </span><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>YES</span></b><span
style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'> (if the test case contains no
contradictions) or </span><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>NO</span></b><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman"'>
(if the input contains contradictions).<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=665 style='width:498.7pt;
 margin-left:2.75pt;border-collapse:collapse;mso-padding-alt:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
 <tr>
  <td width=332 valign=top style='width:249.25pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  border-right:none;padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
  <p class=TableContents style='margin-top:6.0pt;layout-grid-mode:char'><b><span
  style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>Sample Input</span></b><b><span
  style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width=333 valign=top style='width:249.45pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
  <p class=TableContents style='margin-top:6.0pt;layout-grid-mode:char'><b><span
  style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>Sample Output</span></b><b><span
  style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td width=332 valign=top style='width:249.25pt;border-top:none;border-left:
  solid black .25pt;border-bottom:solid black .25pt;border-right:none;
  padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
  <p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>3<br>
  2 2<br>
  big large<br>
  small tiny<br>
  big small<br>
  tiny huge<br>
  2 1<br>
  xyz abc<br>
  abc def <br>
  def xyz<br>
  1 3<br>
  fire flame<br>
  fire ice<br>
  ice water<br>
  water fire<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width=333 valign=top style='width:249.45pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  border-top:none;padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
  <p class=MsoBodyText style='margin-top:6.0pt'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>Case
  1: YES<br>
  Case 2: NO<br>
  Case 3: NO<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>


<div class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center;tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt'>

<hr size=2 width="100%" align=center>

</div>


<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt'><span
style='font-family:Arial'>Problemsetter: Muntasir Azam Khan, Special Thanks:
Sohel Hafiz <o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

</body>

<div class=Section1>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 style='margin-left:2.55pt;
 border-collapse:collapse;mso-padding-alt:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>

 <tr style='height:18.55pt'>
  <td width=278 valign=top style='width:208.45pt;border-top:none;border-left:

 <tr style='height:1.15pt'>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>Once upon a time
there lived an old wise king. He had only one son. The prince had the idea that
he (the prince) was about to be the future king; thats why he became too lazy
day by day. This made the wise king a bit worried because his lazy son couldnt
be the correct man for the throne. He couldnt sleep; his kingdom was in need
of a perfect king, not the lazy king.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>The old king
grew older. One day, while doing his regular works, he found an excellent idea.
The next day he called his son. He said the prince that he wanted the prince to
have his own kingdom. The prince became excited with joy. The king continued
that the prince can have a land from the kings kingdom, but he should start
walking after sunrise and cover a rectangular area before sunset. Then the land
would be given to the prince.</p>

<p class=Textbody style='margin-top:6.0pt;mso-pagination:none'><span
style='mso-fareast-font-family:"DejaVu Sans";mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma;
mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>The lazy prince thought, It would be an easy task!
Thats why he wanted to find the maximum rectangular area in kings land. But
there were some rocks in the kingdom, and the prince didnt want any rocks in
his new land. He would rather take nothing, but no rocks.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>The kings
kingdom can be thought of an <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>m x n</span></b> grid, where <b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>m</span></b>
is the number of rows and <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>n</span></b> is the number of columns. Each
cell in the grid is a small rectangular land whose area is 1. If a land
contains rock it will be denoted by 1, otherwise it will be denoted by 0. The
prince can walk in the sides of the cells and he can either take a cell (land)
or ignore it, but he cant take a part of a cell. Now your task is to find the
maximum rectangular area the prince could cover.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>Input starts
with in integer <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:
"Courier New"'>T (&#8804; 50)</span></b> denoting number of cases.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>Each case starts
with a blank line. Next line contains two integers <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>m</span></b> and <b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>n
(1 &#8804; m, n &#8804; 2000)</span></b> denoting the rows and columns of the
kingdom respectively.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>Each of the next
<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>m</span></b>
lines will contain some integers in the following form</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>k c
p<sub>1</sub> p<sub>2</sub> p<sub>3</sub> ... p<sub>k<o:p></o:p></sub></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>meaning that in
that row, the first <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>p<sub>1</sub></span></b> columns are of type <b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>c</span></b>,
the next <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>p<sub>2</sub></span></b>
columns are of type opposite of <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>c</span></b>, the next <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>p<sub>3</sub></span></b>
columns are of type <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>c</span></b>, the next <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>p<sub>4</sub></span></b>
columns are of type opposite of <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>c</span></b> and so on. You can assume that <b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>c</span></b>
will be either 0 or 1, and opposite of 0 is 1 and vice versa. You can also
assume that <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:
"Courier New"'>p<sub>1</sub> + p<sub>2</sub> + p<sub>3</sub> + ... + p<sub>k</sub>
= n</span></b> and <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>p<sub>i</sub></span></b> is positive.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>Output</span><o:p></o:p></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt'>For each case, print the case
number and the maximum area the prince could cover.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=665 style='width:498.7pt;
 margin-left:2.75pt;border-collapse:collapse;mso-padding-alt:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
 <tr>
  <td width=332 valign=top style='width:249.25pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  border-right:none;padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
  <p class=TableContents style='margin-top:6.0pt;layout-grid-mode:char'><b><span
  style='font-size:14.0pt'>Sample Input</span></b><b><span style='font-size:
  14.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width=333 valign=top style='width:249.45pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>

  </td>

  mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr style='height:1.15pt'>
  <td width=279 valign=top style='width:209.1pt;border-top:none;border-left:
  solid black .25pt;border-bottom:solid black .25pt;border-right:none;
  padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt;height:1.15pt'>
  <p class=TableContents align=right style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:right;
  layout-grid-mode:char'><span style='font-size:10.0pt'>Output</span><span
  style='font-size:10.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
  <td width=296 valign=top style='width:222.1pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  border-top:none;padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt;height:1.15pt'>
  <p class=TableContents style='margin-top:6.0pt;layout-grid-mode:char'><span
  style='font-size:10.0pt'>Standard Output</span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
  mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shapetype
 id="_x0000_t75" coordsize="21600,21600" o:spt="75" o:preferrelative="t"
 path="m@4@5l@4@11@9@11@9@5xe" filled="f" stroked="f">
 <v:stroke joinstyle="miter"/>
 <v:formulas>
  <v:f eqn="if lineDrawn pixelLineWidth 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 1 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum 0 0 @1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @2 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @3 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @0 0 1"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @6 1 2"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelWidth"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @8 21600 0"/>
  <v:f eqn="prod @7 21600 pixelHeight"/>
  <v:f eqn="sum @10 21600 0"/>
 </v:formulas>
 <v:path o:extrusionok="f" gradientshapeok="t" o:connecttype="rect"/>
 <o:lock v:ext="edit" aspectratio="t"/>
</v:shapetype><v:shape id="_x0000_s1032" type="#_x0000_t75" alt="D:\Documents\Programming\Contest\Contest - DIU 2010\Where to Run\robber.png"
 style='position:absolute;left:0;text-align:left;margin-left:0;margin-top:4.5pt;
 width:212.45pt;height:207pt;z-index:1;visibility:visible;
 mso-position-horizontal:left' stroked="t" strokecolor="#4f81bd">
 <v:imagedata src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./e_files/image001.png"  o:title="robber"/>
 <v:textbox style='mso-rotate-with-shape:t'/>
 <w:wrap type="square" anchorx="page"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=286 height=279
src="http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/118/./e_files/image001.png"  align=left hspace=12
alt="D:\Documents\Programming\Contest\Contest - DIU 2010\Where to Run\robber.png"
v:shapes="_x0000_s1032"><![endif]>Last night you robbed a bank but couldnt escape
and when you just got outside today, the police started chasing you. The city,
where you live in, consists of some junctions which are connected by some
bidirectional roads.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>Now since police
is behind, you have nothing to do but to run. You dont know whether you would
get caught or not, but if it is so, you want to run as long as you can. But the
major problem is that if you leave a junction, next time you cant come to this
junction, because a group of police wait there for you as soon as you left it,
while some other keep chasing you.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>Thats why you
have made a plan to fool the police as longer time as possible. The plan is,
from your current junction, you first find the number of junctions which are
safe (no police are there) and if you go to one of them; you are still able to
visit all the safe junctions (in any order) maintaining the above restrictions.
You named them Elected Junction or EJ. If there is no such junction; you stop
running, because you lose your mind thinking what to do, and the police catch
you immediately.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>But if there is
at least one EJ, you can either fool around the police by staying in the
current junction for 5 minutes (actually you just hide there, so the police
lose your track thinking which road you might have taken), or you can choose to
go to any EJ. The probability of choosing to stay in the current junction or to
go to each of the EJ is equal. You can fool the police (by hiding) multiple
times in a city, but of course the above conditions should be satisfied. And you
have decided not to stop in the middle of any road, because you have the fear
that, if you stop in the middle of any road, then the police would surround you
from both ends.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>Now, given the
map of the city and the required time for you to travel each road of the map;
you have to find the expected time for the police to catch you.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt'>Input<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>Input starts
with in integer <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:
"Courier New"'>T (&#8804; 100)</span></b> denoting number of cases.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>Each case starts
with a blank line. Next line contains two integers <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>n (1 &#8804; n &#8804; 15)</span></b>
denoting the number of junctions and <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>m</span></b>, denoting the number of roads in
the city. The junctions are numbered from <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>0</span></b> to <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>n - 1</span></b>.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>Each of the next
<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>m</span></b>
lines contains three integers <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style='font-family:"Courier New"'>u v w (0 &#8804; u, v &lt; n and 0 &lt; w
&#8804; 100 and u &#8800; v)</span></b> meaning that there is a road between
junction <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>u</span></b>
and <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>v</span></b>
and you need <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:
"Courier New"'>w</span></b> minutes to travel the road. Your home is in
junction <b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>0</span></b>
and you are initially in your home. And you may safely assume that there can be
at most one road between a pair of junctions.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:
12.0pt'>Output<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>For each case,
print the case number and the expected time in minutes. Errors less than <b
style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style='font-family:"Courier New"'>10<sup>-5</sup></span></b>
will be ignored.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt'><span style="mso-spacerun:
yes"> </span><span style='font-family:"Liberation Serif";mso-fareast-font-family:
"DejaVu Sans";mso-hansi-font-family:"Liberation Serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=665 style='width:498.7pt;
 margin-left:2.75pt;border-collapse:collapse;mso-padding-alt:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>
 <tr>
  <td width=332 valign=top style='width:249.25pt;border:solid black .25pt;

  <p class=TableContents style='margin-top:6.0pt;layout-grid-mode:char'><b><span

  style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width=333 valign=top style='width:249.45pt;border:solid black .25pt;
  padding:2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt 2.75pt'>

h4
	{mso-style-parent:Standard;
	mso-style-next:Standard;
	margin:0in;
	margin-bottom:.0001pt;

	page-break-after:avoid;

  style='font-size:10.0pt'>Standard Output</span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style='font-family:"Liberation Serif";mso-fareast-font-family:"DejaVu Sans";
mso-hansi-font-family:"Liberation Serif";mso-font-kerning:1.0pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>Alfred is a
researcher and he also likes to give people the largest gift with smallest
possible budget. Being busy in research all the time he cannot go and deliver
his gifts in most cases. Now that his closest friend John is getting married,
so he plans to send him the largest gift box just to surprise John and others
as usual.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'>Alfred has spent
7 long days to buy gifts for his friend and packed all the gifts in nine circular
boxes of equal radius. He now plans to put all of them in a large square shaped
box. He can put them in smallest possible box as shown in Figure 1 but in that
case his gift box would not be as large as he would like it to be. But he
cannot put them in an arbitrary large box because then the circular boxes will
move freely and be damaged while in transport. So now Alfred tries to discover
a way to put nine circular boxes in a largest Possible Square shaped box so
that none of the boxes can move (all are in rigid position). He comes to know
from his researcher friend <span style='mso-bidi-font-size:13.5pt'>Erich</span><span
style='font-size:13.5pt'> </span>the way to put nine circular boxes in largest
possible square shaped box so that none of the circular boxes can move. This is
shown in figure 3.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:6.0pt;text-align:justify'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>
